Even OLD guys like me ... Great band ,so sad when one so young goes .. Remember when they first broke out , woke up alot of old guys like me who thu up every time they heard some  disco, THIS IS WHAT WE HAVE BEEN MISSING .. SAd day , great player , great music.

Yup, big fan of the Beasties... I still remember listening to them on casette tape at my friends house while playing street hockey 25 years ago. Girls and the rest of license to ill blew many speakers..
Loved this band growing up, makes you realize you are aging when the people you idolized growing up are passing away. RIP Adam and Junior.
MCA!  Own a couple Beastie LPs and love everything they've done.  Fantastic musician he was.  Gonna have to put some beasties on the turntable tonight in tribute.  RIP
Luv the Beasties, we are loosing far too many lately
RIP MCA....the topping to a crappy week.
Very sad to hear. The Beasties were a staple of my youth... And tonight we played a bunch in honour of the musical talent and bright light lost.

Bummer.  Loved these guys growing up.  Saw them in Montreal when I was 21 and along with the Chili Peppers they put on the best show.  Used to play bass to alot of their grunge stuff.  "Gratitude" being the first learned, then "Time For Living."  Probably the best hip-hop group and music sampling of all time.  RIP Yauch!
Thanks for that Sinclair!!!! That was awesome.
Sad, one of my favs as a young teen.  Paul Revere, first song I knew beginning to end, and still do .
